The issue is with the while loop syntax. In Zig, the while loop with a continue expression uses a different syntax. The correct syntax is:

```zig
while (condition) : (continue_expression) {
    // body
}
```

But I was trying to use a comma-separated list in the continue expression, which isn't valid. I need to use a block or separate statements properly.

Let me fix the while loops. For counting digits:
```zig
var digits: usize = 0;
var temp = num;
while (temp != 0) {
    digits += 1;
    temp /= 10;
}
```

And for the sum calculation:
```zig
var sum: u128 = 0;
var remaining = num;
const MaxU128: u128 = 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF;

while (remaining != 0) {
    var digit = remaining % 10;
    var digit_pow = int_pow(digit, digits);
    if (sum > MaxU128 - digit_pow) return false;
    sum += digit_pow;
    remaining /= 10;
}
```

Also, the int_pow function has a syntax error - the while loop body needs braces.

